bution to bodily pathology predicted professional help seeking in OCD-anxiety disorder group. In the schizophrenia group, people who believed in psychological causation were more likely to be from higher income group; whereas those who sought professional medical help were more likely to be educated. Conclusion: A wide variety of indigenous beliefs exist in Indo-Pak subcontinent which is in conflict with biomedical models of these psychiatric disorders. Such beliefs result in non-professional medical help seeking which could be detrimental to the health of patients suffering from these psychiatric disorders. (PsycINFO Database Record (c) 2016 APA, all rights reserved)},
